(A) Evidence of erosion and silting. Give extent or percent of stream bed affected:
The upper portions of this system have been quite stable this year.
(B) Particulars of scouring of spawning beds or change in course of stream :
A slight improvement with access to the R/ branch.
(C) Water levels flow, normal, abnorm if. If abnormal, details should be given :
Consistently good water levels through the spawning period.
(D) Particulars of distribution of salmon over strearn bed :
No fish seen in R/H branch. Up to falls at 500 m. in Center branch. Up to 400 m. in L/H branch.
Moderate impact from birds and bears.
(F) Evidence of digging up eggs by late spawning fish :
The R/H branch is still not accessable during low water conditions. Because of the amount of gravel involved, we must wait for the winter floods to make a
